A new season of Business Talk – called Leading with Tech – is coming soon. This season is sponsored by global technology giant Microsoft and leading professional services provider EY, who have partnered to bring insight into the benefits of technology-driven solutions for businesses. The series will be hosted by popular radio and TV personality Michael Avery, who is best known for anchoring the Business Day TV show, the Classic Business show on Classic FM, and the HOT Business show on HOT 1027. Avery will facilitate discussions with key industry experts about important topics such as cyber security, AI, and digital transformation, and his guests will unpack how these and other technologies are crucial to conducting business effectively and efficiently in South Africa. Guests who will appear on the show include: Ritesh Guttoo – EY Africa Cyber Leader
Kavi Pather – EY Africa Artificial Intelligence and Advanced Analytics Leader
Dave Woolnough – EY Africa Partner
Lillian Barnard – Microsoft South Africa Chief Executive Officer Business Talk has been a major success since launching in November 2020, and has already accrued well over a million views. New episodes will be available on the Business Talk website, as well as on BusinessTech’s YouTube and Facebook Pages. These platforms can also be used to watch all previous Business Talk seasons. Watch the trailer below and get ready to learn about Leading with Tech. <span data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start">﻿</span>